hopobject.body: It's serious anabolics.ro.apnpc.com Since 2000, the U.S. National Security Agency has secretly cracked and bypassed much of the digital scrambling hundreds of millions of people rely on to protect the privacy of sensitive data, including medical records, trade secrets, Web searches, Internet chats, and cell and land-line phone calls of Americans and others around the world, the top-secret documents revealed by former NSA contractor Edward Snowden show.
